AI

Sizing the Crypto x AI Market

Sunny Shi
Qorban Ferrell

9 hours ago ⋅  8 min read

Key Insights

  • Since October, AI agent tokens have rapidly proliferated, joining TAO as key players in the emergence of a new and dynamic crypto sector.
  • The Crypto x AI sector is beginning to exhibit the hallmarks of a dominant meta, driven by rising retail participation, a speculative narrative, and favorable market conditions.
  • Prior examples of metas like DeFi in 2020/2021, SOLUNAVAX in 2021, and memecoins in 2023/2024 peaked at collective market caps far exceeding AI's current valuation.
  • Closing 2024 with a ~$14 billion collective market cap, the AI x Crypto sector presents considerable upside, with our base case projecting growth to $100 billion in market cap.

A Brewing AI Bull Market

What should a market sector which combines the explosive liquidity of crypto and the uncapped potential of AI be worth? Since the emergence of GOAT and Truth Terminal in October, projects centered around AI agents and their underlying infrastructure have surged in valuation. We still view Bittensor (TAO) as the leader and early mover in the Crypto x AI space. However, the conversation has shifted away from incentivizing AI models to compete with traditional companies, and more towards leveraging existing models for a direct onchain use case - agents.

With Truth Terminal and early movers like Zerebro, agent capabilities were largely confined to content creation, typically through tweets, generative art and/or occasional music albums. Since then, we’ve seen agent capabilities evolve, from paying humans for work, making self-governed investment decisions, to generating 24/7 crypto research. It is likely that agent utility will see a significant uplift as experimentation continues, and we believe the market is already beginning to price in the implications of this. As evidence, investors are betting on AI agent infrastructure, with platforms like VIRTUAL and AI16Z racing towards multi-billion dollar valuations.

Alongside TAO, a growing number of new agent platforms and individual agent tokens are rapidly gaining both mindshare and market capitalization. The convergence of this emerging narrative with bullish crypto market conditions signals the potential for a new structural “meta” to take hold—one that could dominate crypto growth dynamics in the months ahead. This report aims to examine historical examples of prior market metas and assess the comparative potential of the AI x Crypto sector as it enters this transformative phase.

AI x Crypto - the Makings of a Winner

We see a few parallels for the budding AI x Crypto landscape:

  1. The 2020 / 2021 DeFi Bull Market
  2. The 2021 Solana (SOL) Luna (LUNA) and Avalanche (AVAX) run (colloquially termed SOLUNAVAX)
  3. The 2023 / 2024 memecoin “supercycle”

All three narratives dominated crypto mindshare, saw parabolic price increases, and arose during optimal market conditions. Below, we’ll highlight why AI x Crypto belongs to be situated within this class of market metas.

Retail is Here

The three metas outlined above all thrived due to a high level of retail participation. Similarly, we view the intensifying mindshare in AI x Crypto—primarily driven by the rise of agent coins—as the pivotal factor that has transformed the sector from one struggling to find its footing into a broader market phenomenon. While TAO served as an early catalyst for AI x Crypto attention, its complex subnet architecture, limited user-facing touchpoints, and lack of a native token on Ethereum or Solana made it a challenging proposition for most onchain traders.

The introduction of AI agents marked a turning point, offering users the opportunity to engage with tangible, interactive AI applications while also enabling capital formation behind an explosive amount of new liquid tokens on leading blockchains. As a result of this shift, AI began 2025 commanding nearly 60% X mindshare, as reported by Kaito AI—an all-time high for the sector and a testament to the ongoing progress of retail adoption.

The Right to Dream

The three metas outlined above all benefited from the allure of boundless possibility. In DeFi, the promise of decentralized finance revolutionizing traditional systems unlocked a flood of innovation and speculative investment. The SOLUNAVAX run was fueled by aspirations to find the next big Layer-1 that could flip Ethereum. Meanwhile, memecoins, championed by influencers, offered buyers the hope of investing in assets with seemingly limitless upside. Each narrative was underpinned by the absence of clearly defined limits on potential growth.

In a similar vein, the outline for AI x Crypto taps into this same "right to dream." Today, DeFi applications are assessed against fundamental metrics like revenue multiples, and alternative Layer-1s must demonstrate sufficient usage to justify lofty valuations. In contrast, AI's potential within crypto remains nascent and undefined, offering an open canvas for price appreciation. While speculative premiums may inevitably arise, we believe the value proposition for AI on crypto rails is tangible and compelling (more on our view here). This foundational value could spur rapid growth until the market works out how to properly price these assets over the long term. In short, this could be a re-run of the same movie, and we’ve seen the climax before.

The Timing is Right

Prior metas typically rise in tandem with a significant upward move in BTC's price, often peaking shortly after a BTC all-time high is breached. Analyzing our precedents:

  • Our DeFi index followed along with BTC’s ascent from $10,000 to above $60,000 during 2020/2021, reaching its market cap peak a month after BTC achieved a new all-time high of $63,000 in April 2021.
  • SOLUNAVAX followed BTC’s second surge from approximately $30,000 to over $68,000 in November 2021, similarly peaking around a month after BTC’s new all-time high.
  • Memecoins moved in sync with BTC in 2023 and 2024, experiencing strong growth after BTC broke through $73,000 in March 2024, and again as BTC surpassed $100,000 in December 2024.

While past performance is not indicative of future results, the key takeaway is that each of these narratives was driven by periods of positive BTC price performance, either leading up to or during their parabolic moves. The early growth of the AI x Crypto market cap appears to align with BTC’s all-time high break in December, and should BTC’s price continue to rise or remain stable from this point forward, we believe the conditions within the crypto market will be highly supportive for a new meta to take hold.

Making the Comparisons

Let’s compare our Crypto x AI Index, which consists of TAO and leading agent tokens, to the winning narratives in prior cycles. As of December 31st, the AI index’s circulating market cap stood at ~$14 billion.

DeFi vs. AI

Our DeFi index, which includes the top 15 representative DeFi tokens from 2020/2021, reached a collective market cap of over $60 billion in April 2021 after breaking the $10 billion mark in August 2020. The seasonal parallels between DeFi in 2020 and AI in 2024 are particularly noteworthy.

SOLUNAVAX vs. AI

SOLUNAVAX reached a collective market cap of over $120 billion in December 2021 after crossing the $10 billion mark in March 2021.

Memes vs. AI

Our memecoin index, which consists of the top 50 memes of 2023/2024 excluding DOGE and SHIB, reached a collective market cap of over $40 billion in December of 2024, after crossing the $10 billion mark in March of 2024.

Comparing Market Share

When looking at market share AI remains underpenetrated relative to prior metas at their peak, currently sitting at less than 0.5% of total crypto market capitalization.

Conclusion

“History doesn’t repeat itself, but it often rhymes” - Mark Twain

The growth trajectory for Crypto x AI valuations is likely to be unique, as it has been for previous crypto narratives. However, when comparing AI’s current crypto market cap of ~$14 billion to our case studies, the upside potential is substantial.

To forecast some initial outcomes, we project some scenarios for where the sector may shake up in 2025:

  • Base Case: Crypto’s total market cap remains stable at $3.3 trillion, with AI taking share from other sectors. Assuming AI is able to capture 3% market share (similar to DeFi in 2021 and Memecoins in 2024), total Crypto x AI market cap grows to ~$100 billion.
  • Bear Case: Crypto total market cap contracts 25%, with AI losing half of its current market share. Total Crypto x AI market cap shrinks to just ~$5 billion.
  • Bull Case: A crypto bull market causes total crypto market cap to grow 25%, largely driven by AI tokens. Assuming AI is able to capture 5% market share (similar to SOLUNAVAX in 2021), total Crypto x AI market cap grows to ~ $207 billion.

Similar to speculative cycles in the past, we believe Crypto x AI is currently undergoing a stage where price is beginning to outpace fundamentals. While this report is focused more on the former over the latter, continued evolution in Crypto x AI’s product-market-fit (PMF) will be needed to justify growing prices. However, in crypto, price speculation often precedes the realization of true PMF—a pattern that played out in both the DeFi boom and the L1 trade of 2021. We believe the AI narrative in 2025 will follow a similar trajectory, delivering multiples of growth across a broad selection of tokens before the market identifies and filters for long-term winners that can sustain their value.
